{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-term-tsx-content-file-path-terms-brand-and-campaign-rejections-index-md","path":"/glossary/brand-and-campaign-rejections/","result":{"data":{"mdx":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Brand and Campaign Rejections"},"body":"In order to send messages on local or 10-digit long code (10DLC) numbers in North America, your numbers need to be registered with The Campaign Registry (TCR). \n\nAs part of TCR registration process you must register all of the [Brands](/glossary/brand/ \"/glossary/brand/\") that will be listed underneath your business. Brands = your customers that the messages will be coming from. And you must register all of the [Campaigns](/glossary/campaign/ \"/glossary/campaign/\") underneath those Brands. Campaigns = the messaging use cases your customers leverage i.e. marketing, appointment reminders, alerts, etc. \n\nOnce you are registered as a CSP with TCR, all of the information you shared about your customers and their use cases, AKA your Brands and Campaigns, need to be vetted for accuracy by Direct Connect Aggregators (DCAs) and either approved or rejected.\n\nIf one thing is out of place, from anything as small as a typo to a larger problem like no opt-in language on your customer’s website, that will lead to a rejection. \n\nTo avoid TCR Brand and Campaign rejections and ensure TCR approval, [please refer to the following guide](/news/brand-campaign-rejections/ \"/news/brand-campaign-rejections/\").","id":"fb516d7b-e613-50b5-aaf0-a362bd0602cf","fields":{"slug":"brand-and-campaign-rejections/"},"excerpt":"In order to send messages on local or 10-digit long code (10DLC) numbers in North America, your numbers need to be registered with The Campaign…"},"allMdx":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Toll-Free Numbers"},"id":"59cde07c-8cd8-5ed1-a34c-9aecaa4812b7","fields":{"slug":"toll-free-numbers/"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Time Routing"},"id":"ca8b85e6-8f5d-521d-b646-7c5e4cabd4ac","fields":{"slug":